inn1.comm: angling it down leg, tries to work it down, is hit on the thighs
shaping away nicely, left Butt as he came forward, he shoulders arms to that one
probing him on the off, good length, gets forward and drops it in front of the bowler
a touch fuller outside off, gets across and works it wide of midwicket
on the stumps, bang on target, bowled on a good length, defended back onto the pitch, nice start by Bracken here
starts off with a maiden, tries to turn it down the leg side and calls for a single, but midwicket runs in to prevent it
good bounce, bowled at 136 kmph, banged in short outside off, backs away
beaten, a driving length outside off and moves away just as he is tempted to play it through the line
loose ball on the leg stump, it's full and he cashes in, clips it off his pads through square leg to get off the mark in style
short of a good length on the off and jagging back in, defended solidly towards cover
the inswinger again, on middle and off, presents the full face and drives it back, looked good so far this newbie
too high, nipped back in to strike him on the thighs as he tried to whip that away, bowling consistently at around 136 kmph
short of a good length outside off, comes down and tempts the audience into thinking he'll play a cut, shoulders arms
a touch fuller this time and Butt is drawn forward again, tries to slap that past cover, fails to connect
good length on the off, walks across and drops it dead on the off side
short and wide, slashed down to third man, a touch slower than his partner Bracken, around 131 kmph

run out, utter confusion, both the batsmen have stood their ground after ending up at the same end. Turned to square leg and Shehzad immediately set off, Butt also responded but turned back after getting halfway down the pitch, he crossed Shehzad who kept running. An accurate throw to the striker's end, and Haddin clips the bails.
good length on the off, pushed straight to cover
on middle and leg, pushed into the leg side off the back foot
slashes hard, chases it but fails to connect, left him and bounced more than he expected
oversteps, a bit more effort there, guided to third man
misses out, bowled it full and wide, almost yorker length, salvages a single as he digs it out wide of mid-off
testing line outside off and swinging away, shoulders arms to it
short of a good length outside off, left alone
a touch fuller, teasing him outside off, leaves it be once again

almost another run out, Clarke had all the time in the world to take aim and score a direct hit at the non-striker's end but missed, pushed straight to him at cover and they've survived a chance here as they attempted a single
on the off stump, gets forward and dabs it to cover
deliberately done, much fuller outside off, gets his front foot across and jabs it with an open face, takes the edge and flies over the slips
fuller outside off, much closer to the off stump this time, left him as he played slightly inside the line
brought it back in this time, outside off again, Butt judged it to perfection, letting it go
reaches forward and punches it to cover, held its line this time
getting it to move back in quite sharply, catches him high on the pads as he tries to fend that away
slightly overpitched on the off stump, tries to drive it hard with a flourish, mistimes it straight to cover
short on the off, punched off the back foot to cover, quiet start by the 'hosts' here
beaten, a little slower, bowled at 126.4 kmph, a legcutter that spat away as he got to the pitch to drive
beauty! Almost did him in with the inswinger, mixing it up nicely, nipped back in from outside off and shot up over middle as Younis swung across the line
a touch too straight, on middle and leg, tucked behind square, another quiet over
straying on the pads, tickled to fine leg for a single
good length on the off, gets forward, bends low and guides it down to third man
fuller on the off, pushed watchfully to cover
closes the face and dabs it down towards midwicket, calls for a single but is sent back wisely
gave him the charge, was not quite to the pitch but struck it firmly over the catcher on the off side for a pressure-relieving boundary
restrains himself this time, it's on a cutting length but he opts to let it go
turned away to square leg off the back foot, they've managed to keep the lid on the runs here
short on the off, pushes it short of point and calls for a single when it isn't there, he's been kept quiet here
does well this time, jumps up on him, leaps on squeezes it down to third man
lucky, the bowler deserved a wicket there, drew him forward with a tempting line outside off, Butt pushed at it hard, wasn't to the pitch, got a thick edge well wide of second slip, Bolly's done well
held its line, bowled straight on the off, pushed to cover from the crease, his footwork has not been too convincing
firmly struck, got to the pitch this time but failed to beat the gap, struck it straight to mid-off
bowled at 133 kmph, dropped down to cover off the front foot
on middle and off, gets behind it nicely and pushes it back on the pitch
good length on the off stump, stays back  and punches it to cover, mistimed it there, struggling to get a move-on here
tries to force it back past the bowler here but fails, Bracken fields well on the follow  through, the pressure's building now, especially on Younis

edged and survives, the ploy almost works, overpitched and moved away, went after it, wasn't to the pitch, got a thick edge just wide of a diving slip, that should ease some nerves though he was in a spot of bother there
gets forward and bunts it straight to cover, Bracken unlucky
short on middle, holding its line, jabbed to midwicket
pushed through fuller, gets to the pitch and turns it to midwicket once again
slightly short, moves back and chops it down to third man
excellent shot, he's looked a little rusty but this was exquisite, it's not overpitched but he picks it well, getting forward and square-driving it between cover and point, that should get him going
on the front foot and pushes it wide of midwicket for a single
overpitched on the off, closes the face slightly and dabs it to midwicket
on middle and off, gets across and defends it back to the bowler, Bracken continues to be miserly
short on middle, gets a thick inside edge to fine leg as he looks to punch that off the back foot
fuller on the off stump, bowled at 129.5 kmph, gets to the pitch and pushes it to cover
on middle and off, cramping him for room there, defended to cover
on middle and off, gets across and pushes it in front of cover
short of a good length on the off, chopped down to point, nice steady bowling here, they've given nothing away, too few four balls
just as I said they were accurate, short outside off and Younis cashes in, gets back and punches it crisply between cover and mid-off
full on the off, Younis gets to the pitch and drives it with a full face down the ground past the bowler for another boundary, getting a move-on now
similar delivery, firmly struck again but mid-off does well to dive full length to his right to save a couple of runs
good length on the off stump, defended cautiously in front of mid-off

appeal for lbw, round the wicket into the left hander, struck him on the pads as he walked across to whip it wide of midwicket, looked really close but the umpire thought it was going down, we need another replay
tries to tuck it away behind square, gets a legbye as it brushes his thighs
short of a good length on the off, defended to cover off the front foot
full on the off, crashed to point, fails to beat the gap, he has to give Younis the strike here
he's getting a little frustrated, good length again, took a couple of steps and tried to force it past cover, mistimed it
Butt gets across and tries to swing across the line in the direction of square leg, is struck on the pads, struggling a bit, Butt
stump-to-stump, on the off, defended back to Bracken, good tight stuff
jumped on him but he handled it well, getting on top of it and nudging it down to third man
good length on the off stump, punches it straight to cover, the grind continues
full, pushes it wide of mid-off and sets off for a quick single, Younis responds well
good length on the off, gets forward and pushes it towards short cover
poor ball really, full on the pads, tickles it really fine and earns another four, he's done well here, recovered nicely after a shaky start
on middle and leg, pushed through the line to mid-on
short of a length on the off, punched between point and cover, there is a single for the taking but the batsmen decide against it
short on the off, dabbed back to the bowler
on middle and off, gets back and drops it down to cover, is sent back

fell short of Symonds, just short, driven straight to him and dived forward and took it on the half-volley, a sign of desperation there, went through with the short even though it wasn't quite there to hit
finally, just a fraction wide, enough to free his arms and he moves away to chip it over mid-off for a boundary, took him quite a while, was bogged down for a bit
gets back and chops it wide of point for single
back of a length on the off, defended in front of mid-off
tossed up on the off, drives it through the line to long-off
outside off, gets across and drives it down to midwicket
flighted on the off, charges down and drills it down to long-off
short of a good length on middle, goes on straight, dropped dead on the off side
plats his foot forward and pushes it back to the bowler
fullish on leg stump, bends low and drives it to midwicket, nice start
he strikes immediately! A tame dismissal really, short and wide, goes for the cut, swings away as he plays the shot, takes the outside edge and Haddin makes no mistake
good length on the off and moving away, gets forward and defends, back to tuk tuk cricket
or maybe not, slightly short on middle, turned away to fine leg to get off the mark
well struck, sweetly timed, slower ball bowled full outside off, drove it firmly past a diving cover for a couple
straight to the fielder this time, full on the off, bunts it down to mid-off
short and wide, held its line, slashed away to third man
tossed up on the off, drives that inside-out towards deep cover
flat on the off stump, not much spin for this guy so far, defended with a lunge to cover

misfield, concedes four runs, flighted and Malik was tempted, he charged down the track and smashed it wide of Bollinger, he should have covered it, fell just short, but failed to get his body behind it

dropped, short and wide, cut away but uppishly and straight to Watson at point where he bent low to his right but failed to clutch it, was dying on him but he wasn't quick enough to react, Malik survives again
pushed through cover for a single
short of a good length on the off, dabbed down to cover
on middle and off, covers the movement well by moving across and guiding it to point
fullish on middle, takes a step across and pushes it to midwicket, slow going for Butt here
full on the pads, flicked away to deep square leg for a single, he's looked a little stiff today, hasn't been able to rotate the strike too often
slightly short outside off, chopped down to third man from the crease
pushed through a little quick on the off, drives it back to the bowler
gave it some more air this time, gets the same result
and again, defended this time, watchfully, towards Hauritz
thrown up on the off stump, reaches forward and defends towards cover

well caught by Haddin, bowled it a touch flat outside off, Malik charged down the pitch and had a massive swing at it, got the inside edge as it spun in, hit the boot and lobbed up in front of Haddin who dived to pluck it inches from the ground, it's been referred to the third umpire who rightly gives it OUT after taking ages to come up with a decision, though it looked pretty straightforward. It didn't flash on the screen, the buttons don't seem to be working, but the message is out to the players in the middle
short of a length outside off, spun in just a fraction, defended to cover
poor line, straying on the pads, its clipped down wide of fine leg for a couple, Butt's the anchor man now
overpitched, driven but not entirely committed to the shot, just a firm push to mid-off
excellent shot! Full and wide, leaned forward and creamed it wide of mid-off, gift ball but he executed it brilliantly
short of a good length, dabbed wide of point, there is a single but they take it after much deliberation
swung back in but wide enough for him to leave it alone, good length and he just let it through
fullish on the off, tries to drive it through the line, hits the inside half of the bat and rolls down to midwicket
tossed up outside off, gets forward and slashes it behind point, opened the face at the last moment, gets a couple
on the off stump, dipping into the left hander, dropped back on the pitch
is down the track and drives it down to long-off
bowled with a flatter trajectory outside off, walks across and paddles it really fine to beat short fine to the boundary, nice improvisation
on and outside of, defends it with a reach to cover
quicker one bowled full on the off, pushed to midwicket
good length on the off, holding its line, taps it to cover

close shout for lbw, Rauf is unmoved, short of a good length on the off and nipped back in sharply, caught Butt by surprise as he came forward to defend, got the faintest of inside edges onto the pads though he was struck in line, good decision in the end
short on middle and leg and angling down, tries to whip it behind square and is struck on the pads again
back of a length on the off and came back in, defended wide of the bowler
full on middle and leg, gets under it and drives it to a widish mid-on, getting some good movement here Bolly
short outside off, gets back and runs it down to third man
flat on the off stump, punched straight to cover
slightly short on the off, opens the face to guide it to point
presents the full face and bunts it down to long-off
gave it some air, bowled slightly short, spun in and he defends it to midwicket
flighted outside off, gets outside the line and tickles it down to square leg
good fielding at midwicket, pushed wide of him and they think of a second but he slides and returns a good throw to keep them to just a single, Australia have tightened things up nicely here
Bolly fires it in a t137.2 kmph, just a fraction full on the off, played to midwicket
a touch full on the off, decent pace that, 137.4 kmph, bends and punches that to mid-off
banged it in short, consistent speeds here, leapt up to Misbah who dropped it down with soft hands
back of a length on middle, turned behind square for a single
on middle and leg, and getting it to move back in, defended short of midwicket
pushed through on a good length on middle, dropped on the off side, sent back, well done Bolly
on middle and off, gets forward and defends
innovation, full and wide, reverse-sweeps it wide of short third, well done
pushed through to midwicket off the front foot
on middle, tossed up, is tempted, but only for a second as he restrains himself to just push it back to the bowler
short outside off, fired in quick, gets back and cuts it behind point for a couple more
on the off stump, held its line, dropped it dead on the pitch, Hauritz has contained them well
quicker one bowled full on leg stump, played back to him
his eyes lit up there, full and wide, gave it some air as well, bent low and smashed it wide of cover, powerfully struck
a tad overpitched on the off, pushed back to Symonds
nicely done, gets forward, opens the face to beat short third man, Laughlin gives chase and dives full length forward to drag it back just inside the ropes
came on really slowly, moves across to paddle it down for a single
tossed up on middle and off, pushed back to a diving Symonds
gives Butt the strike, favouring the paddle here, plays it towards deep square leg
drifting into the leg stump, pushed away to deep square leg to bring up his 11th ODI fifty, a bit of a laboured effort here, not at his fluent best but he needs to bat till the end now

Misbah goes for the reverse-sweep and finds David Husey at short third, quicker on outside off and he tries to help it on its way, went really quickly towards Hussey to dived full length to his right to pluck a sharp one, stayed alert throughout
too straight first up, on middle, turned away to deep square leg
on middle and off, dropped short of the bowler, the pressure's back on Butt now
drifting in, full on middle, dabbed back to the bowler
bang on target and is treated with respect, swinging in towards middle, gets back and defends solidly
was not to the pitch, but these rules don't apply to Afridi, swatted it wide of mid-off for a single, didn't time it well enough
full on middle, bowled at 139.7 kmph, a touch quicker than normal, died on him but he did well to bring his bat down in time
back of a length on the off, dropped down to point, the scoring rate continues to dip
bowled from wide of the crease, bowled it a little slower, at 129 kmph, pushed straight to mid-on
good length on the off and moved back in, defended back to the bowler, Bolly continues to impress
tossed up outside off, moves well across and nudges it to short fine
short on the off, gets back and punches it to long-on
short of a length, cuts it straight to short third

dropped by Laughlin, straightforward chance, sucked him in with the flight, lofted it straight to long-off where Laughlin, who's come too far in and spills it while trying to take it over his head, ends up palming it to the boundary, how costly will that prove?
on middle and off, pushed in front of cover
cut away wide of point for a single to keep the strike
low full toss on middle, mistimes a heave to deep midwicket
short on middle, gets back and defends it to midwicket, calls for a single but is sent back
short of a good length on the off, dropped short of point
slower one on middle and leg, worked away behind square
short of a good length on the off, dropped it short of point off the back foot, Bolly's been difficult to get away here, done a fine job in his first game
slower one bowled on a good length on middle, at 127.5 kmph, defended to cover
tossed up on the off from round the wicket, pushed back to the bowler
beats the diving cover, drives it inside-out into the deep, couple
flatter on the off, gets forward and dabs it to cover
slightly short on the off, opens the face to guide it to short third
flat on middle and off, not much spin but maintaining a tight line here, defended back to the bowler
flighted on the off, driven down the ground to long-off to keep the strike
short on middle, gets back and nudges it behind square, thinks of a second but they opt against it wisely
goes for it, bowled short, a bouncer on middle, at 136.1 kmph, he tries to hook it but it's quick and bounces a little too high
back of a length, makes room and creams that to deep cover
fullish on the off stump, slower one that, at 116.7 kmph, bunts it down the ground to long-off
full and wide, waits for it, bends low and steers it wide of third man, not able to beat him though, settles for a single
overpitched on middle, pushed to midwicket
flat and short on leg stump, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
flighted on middle, defended to cover off the front foot
Hauritz takes three, dipped into him and appeared to stop on him a little, chips it, with hardly any conviction, straight to Symonds who dives forward at cover
on middle and off, pushed back onto the pitch
short of a length outside off, guided wide of point for a single
deliberately done, not the best end to the spell but he's done well, short and wide, slashes at it to beat short third to the boundary
beaten, a touch too quick perhaps, zipped past him as he tried to defend that off the back foot
fullish on the off, bowled at133 kmph, driven straight to mid-off
back of a length on the off, punched to cover
a touch too wide there, slightly short, runs it down to third man
slower ball, at 115.5 kmph, on leg stump, was probably going down as he missed a pull, should have dismissed that, will be ruing it now
swung back in, got forward and drove it firmly to mid-off, interesting appeal that, the bowler probably thought it was pad first, but if it was, it appeared to strike him outside the line
short of a good length on middle, tries to force it through the leg side, is struck on the ribs
short on middle and leg, gets back and plays it back to the bowler
that was coming, just a fraction short, made room and sliced it away to third man, didn't time it well
moved away, good length outside off, inviting him into the drive, zipped away to beat the outside edge, good stuff
short on middle, gets back and pulls it to deep square leg
nice finish to the over, bouncer banged in on middle, ducks under it
first four in a while, fraction full and he went after it, got a thick edge wide of the keeper for a boundary
slower ball bowled full on the off, driven firmly with a flourish to deep cover, couple more, opening up now
brought it back in, landed on a good length on the off, defended firmly to cover
short, plays away from his body, steers it to third man
shot, but there's cover in the deep, overpitched on the off, drilled down the ground to long-off
short on the off, gets back and drops it short of cover
full on middle, swings it away towards deep square leg, a low full toss that, didn't get hold of it
short of a good length on the off, steady pace, 131.5 kmph, drops it short of point
well struck, just a fraction full, made room and caressed it past a diving cover, hit it uppishly but was in the gap, important runs these
good length on middle, defends it to cover off the back foot
on middle and leg, gets across and chips it wide of mid-on
kept a little low, slower one at 118.6 kmph, played away to third man
short of a good length on middle, defended to cover, had shaped himself for an expansive shot there but it moved back in, hence the adjustment
shot away off the pitch, not a lot of movement, but enough to beat his prod away from the body
shortish on middle, gets back and tickles it to fine leg for a single
came back in, played short of Clarke at point and they're off
tries to be cheeky, good length outside off, stays his ground and tries to run it down , misses
misses again, has a mighty heave over midwicket, fails to get anywhere near it
full on the off, gets to it and slices it over cover, long-off takes time to cut that off and they've taken two
short on middle, played wide of midwicket for a single
short of a length, makes room and slash that over point, misses
he's got under it nicely, was in the slot, slower ball bowled full on the off, meaty, and he smashed it over long-on, came off the middle
they're cashing in now, short and wide, bisects the gap between point and cover to find the boundary, got forward and punched it firmly
low full toss on the off, pushed it to cover, missed out there
gone! Bowled on a length on middle, walks across and chips it straight to David Hussey at midwicket, mistimed there, had tried to clear him, six down.
starts off nicely, gifted with a length ball outside off and he leans into the drive, playing it like a batsman to beat the covers
on middle and leg, defended off the front foot back to the bowler
slower ball bowled short outside off, at 123 kmph, is into the shot too early, misses
good length on the off stump, gets a thick inside edge wide of midwicket and rushes off for a single, shy at the stumps but Gul is well in
short on the off, drops it short of cover and steals a single to keep the strike
poor fielding by Hauritz, short and wide, reaches for it and dabs it wide of short third where Hauritz dives over it and lets it through the gate
nicely done, short and wide, slashes hard, gets a thick edge to the third-man boundary
slower one bowled full on the off, driven down the ground to long-on
bouncer, banged in short on the off, ducks under it
attempted bouncer again, short outside off, Gul backs away, two dot balls
short on the off, he ducks, wasn't that the second one of the over? No signal from the umpire
length ball outside off and he misses out on his attempt to clear cover, swung hard, missed
nipped back in, bowled short outside off from wide of the crease and came back in to beat the outside edge as he tried to run that down

edged and Haddin flings himself to his right to snap that out of thin air, superb catch! Fraction full on the off, makes room while simultaneously stepping out, tries to launch it over the in-field on the off side, gets a thick edge and the keeper pulls off a beauty. Big blow that!
short of a good length on the off, defended to cover

dropped, Rameez says "Hauritz was horrible", skied it, slower ball and he tried to clear long-on, mistimed it and Hauritz ran back but never really got under it, tough chance that, it was getting away from him, Rameez should have been in his shoes
banged in short on middle, Gul ducks under it

missed run out, Haddin was really horrible, swatted to mid-off, an accurate throw all along the ground to the striker's end as Shoaib is struggling to make it, and he lets it through, a bit of a bad bounce but he should have collected that
pays the price,  fullish, makes room and slices it over point, nicely done
and another one, struck really firmly this time, full on the off and he carts it over the covers, all these add up
back of a length on middle, came back in, pushed to point, decides against the single
had a massive heave at that one, went downtown but missed, just left him, was in the slot though
good length on the off, angled down to third man for a single
beaten outside off, prodding at it, trying to nudge it down to third man, misses
poor ball, low full toss on the off stump, makes room and just chips it over cover all the way to the boundary, sweetly struck, Shoaib has done wonderfully well thus far
tries to be play smart, short on middle, made room to edge that wide of the keeper, missed
that's disappeared, Hopes is getting the treatment, just a fraction short on the off, he makes way and swats it with contempt well over long-on
cheeky, slower one bowled full outside off, he reaches for it to slice it over point and beat a diving third man, 200 up, another 25-30 runs and they would have done really well
short on middle, whips it away wide of deep square leg, the buzz is back
on middle and leg, pushed towards long-on for a single to give Shoaib the strike
pushed in quick on the off, tried to slog-sweep that into the stands, mistimes it to long-on

flighted outside off, bent down, got down on one knee to sweep that over square leg, got the top edge and Hauritz ran well to his left from deep square leg, timed his dive well, and made amends for that drop earlier
superb catch by Clarke! Short on the off, gets back and punches it hard, almost clears cover but Clarke leaps and plucks it with his left hand out of thin air to send Shoaib back
tossed up outside off, gets forward and pushes it to cover
on middle and leg, turned away behind square
run out, tapped to point, too much hesitation, Iftikhar calls for a single and decides against it midway through the run, Clarke returns it to Bracken who takes off the bails to find Ajmal well short

inn2.comm: loosener, bowled at 135.7 kmph, short and wide, moving away further, left alone
beat the outside edge this time, short of a good length and zipped away, pretended to withdraw from the shot but too late
slightly wide of the crease, angling into the right hander, gets back and turns it down to square leg, clocked 140 kmph there
spat of the pitch, excellent carry through to the keeper, settling into his rhythm nicely there, moved away and Akmal collected it over his head
beaten, banged it in on a length outside off and moved away as he pushed at it off the back foot, 142 kmph, getting pacier by the ball
short of a good length on the off and moved away to just evade the outside edge, bowled at 143.5 kmph there, good start
in the channel outside off stump, held its line, moved across and tapped it to cover
almost chopped it on, 135.2 kmph, played away from his body there, got an inside edge onto his pads, called for a single but was sent back
bouncer banged in on middle, he ducks under it well
short of a length on the off, gets back and punches it to point
shot, just a fraction short, gets forward and punches it firmly between cover and point for three runs
nipped back in, landed short outside off, he stood tall and dabbed it towards cover
getting some good movement away, bowling from wide of the crease and firing it into the right hander, pushed at it, played inside the line and got a thick edge down to third man
nicely timed, short on middle, gets back and pushes it firmly through the big gap between square leg and midwicket, three more, a touch too straight there
straying in line, down the leg side this time, wide, the first of the match
back of a length on the off, gets half-forward and taps it to cover
that's fast, bowled at 145.5 kmph, too quick for Hopes, tried to fend it away as it jagged back in, struck him high on the pads
quicker, 146.3 kmph, but slightly misdirected, short on leg stump, tries to clip it fine, misses out, salvages another leg bye
short of a length on the off, punches it to cover off the back foot
short of a good length on middle, gets back, stands tall and plays it back to Gul, gentle medium in comparison, 133.7 kmph
smashed, seized the length quickly, fraction short on the off, pulled it away over square leg, cautious start but he's not going to waste those
shortish again, on the off stump, gets it wide of midwicket for a single
was in the air, but safe, they seem to be handling Gul much more comfortably here, full outside off, gets forward and slices it down to third man
atrocious shot! Good length on the off, he made room and tried to heave that over the leg-side field, missed and the offstump was pegged back, deserves to go!
poked at it, ran it down to third man for a single
good length on the off, at 141.5 kmph, dropped dead on the pitch
sweetly struck but straight to the fielder, short on the off, punched to cover off the back foot
zipped through, was too quick on Watson, 144 kmph, just marginally outside off, didn't get his bat down in time, sped past the outside edge
tried to drive it through the line towards mid-off, ended up getting a thick edge down to third man
short of a good length on the off, defended to mid-off
much straighter, pushed it back to Shoaib who palmed it wide of cover or a single
Gul got that to jump off the pitch and smack his gloves must have hurt, dropped on the off side, fiery spell by these two
short on the off stump, defended with a full face back to the bowler
dropped, was a tough one, stopped on Hopes who pushed it back uppishly towards the bowler, Gul reached for it stretching to his left, was a little slow to react there, and palmed it onto the ground
whipped away off his hips wide of midwicket for a single
needs to get fuller here, no trouble dabbing it down to third man
struck on the ribs there, has settled in nicely Shoaib, on middle, tried to turn that away but again, didn't manage to counter the 143 kmph delivery all too well
punishes this one, short and wide, waits for it and cuts it away fiercely over point, third man had no chance
